The parental NTERA-2 lines was established in 1980 from a nude mouse xenograft of the Tera-2 cell line (see ATCC HTB-106). The NTERA-2 cl.D1 cell line is a pluripotent human testicular embryonal carcinoma cell line derived by cloning the NTERA-2 cell line.
